  "instructions": [
    "Heat 20g of ghee in the lazy-susan-spinner over medium heat, approximately 4 minutes, or until the ghee reaches 160C.",
    "Add 45g of ginger garlic paste, stir until fragrant, approximately 1 minute.",
    "Add 50ml of kombu-cold-extract and 400ml of bone broth, and bring to a simmer.",
    "Add 200g of buckwheat groats and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and cover the lazy-susan-spinner, approximately 20 minutes.",
    "Stir in 0.8g turmeric, 0.4g cayenne pepper, and 0.6g black pepper.",
    "Season with salt to taste.",
    "Garnish with 20g of fresh parsley and 20g of fresh cilantro, and serve hot.",
    "Drizzle with 30ml of lemon juice and serve immediately.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional parsley and cilantro if desired.",
    "Serve as a comforting and pungent dinner option, suitable for keto diet."
